      • convert

        public static java.lang.String convert(int aggFuncType)
        Returns a String representation of the type of aggregate function that is present.
        Parameters:
        aggFuncType - The integer stored in the CypReturn object (view CypherTranslator for more information).
        Returns:
        String meaning of the integer input (usually from the CypReturn getAggFunc() method.)

      • sqlEquiv

        public static java.lang.String sqlEquiv(int aggFuncType)
        Returns the SQL equivalent syntax for the aggregate function being used. Mostly this is a straightforward of the same keyword (i.e. sum() in Cypher unsurprisingly maps to sum() in SQL). collect() in Cypher however becomes array_agg() in Postgres at least.
        Parameters:
        aggFuncType - The integer stored in the CypReturn object (view CypherTranslator for more information).
        Returns:
        SQL syntax for the aggregate function represented by the integer argument.
